{{Infobox Hindu leader | name = Bangaru Adigalar | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1941|3|3|mf=y}}| | birth_place = Maruvathur, [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]| | death_date = | death_place = | order = | guru = | disciples = | philosophy = | signature = }} '''Bangaru Adigalar''' is a South [[India]]n spiritual guru. He is the President of [[ACMEC|Adiparasakthi Charitable Medical Educational and Cultural Trust]]. He is called 'Amma', meaning mother in Tamil, by his followers and devotees of the Adhiparasakthi temple. He speaks Oracles, perform miracles & when followed by his followers, walks in an effeminate fashion.He is believed to be the incarnation of the Supreme power – ADHIPARASAKTHI by his followers. He has huge followers and they all are believers of AMMA. Bangaru adigalar has implemented reforms in temple and spiritualism.
