{{more footnotes|date=September 2018}}
This is a '''list of the deadliest Atlantic [[hurricane]]s''', including all known storms that caused at least 1,000 direct deaths. The deadliest Atlantic hurricane in recorded history was the [[Great Hurricane of 1780]], which resulted in 22,000–27,501 fatalities. In recent years, the deadliest hurricane was [[Hurricane Mitch]] of [[1998 Atlantic hurricane season|1998]], with at least 11,374 deaths attributed to it.

== Pre-[[HURDAT]] era ==
